# Task 26 follow-up ‚Äî compose smoke ‚Äúhang‚Äù resolution (2026-03-20)

## Root cause (smoke script)

`scripts/compose-smoke.sh` polled `GET /sessions/:id` until `status == "completed"`.

For `workflow: "chat"`, the server intentionally sets session `status` to **`running`** after a successful job completion so clients can POST follow-up input (`POST /sessions/:id/input`). This is implemented in `crates/server/src/worker_tasks.rs` (`session_status` branch for `workflow == "chat"`).

Integration proof: `crates/server/tests/sessions_integration.rs` ‚Äî `chat_session_create_pull_complete_and_follow_up_input` asserts `detail2.status == "running"` after `complete` while `jobs[0].status == "completed"`.

The worker was not stuck for 300s waiting on HTTP; the script‚Äôs exit condition was never satisfiable for a single-turn chat session.

## Smoke script fix

- Poll until either `status == "completed"` OR (`workflow == "chat"` AND exactly one job AND `jobs[0].status == "completed"`).
- Timeout message updated to ‚Äúterminal success‚Äù wording.

Verified: `./scripts/compose-smoke.sh` exits 0 (‚âà5m first run with image build; subsequent runs faster with cache).

