## Worker / Docker hardening (still valuable for real file:// on Docker Desktop)

These changes remain in the tree from debugging bind-mount + libgit2 behavior; they do not change the chat session lifecycle but reduce risk of blocking I/O on `file://` remotes:

- `Dockerfile.worker`: install `git`; runtime `ARG RH_DOCKER_SRC_TS` echo before `COPY` binary (cache bust).
- `Dockerfile`: runtime `ARG RH_DOCKER_SRC_TS` echo (server image).
- `crates/worker/src/git_ops.rs`:
  - `file://` clone via `git clone --no-hardlinks` + `Repository::open`.
  - `checkout_ref` uses git CLI when file-remote semantics apply.
  - `session_repo_url` threaded into `checkout_ref`, `current_branch_name`, `head_oid_hex`, `working_tree_clean` via `use_file_remote_semantics` so the task‚Äôs URL wins over libgit2 `origin` metadata.
  - For file remotes: branch name + HEAD OID from `.git` files (+ packed-refs fallback); `working_tree_clean` short-circuit when stub agent + `REMOTE_HARNESS_STUB_NO_TOUCH_FILE` (compose smoke).
  - `GitOpsError::GitCli` for CLI failures.
- `crates/worker/src/task_execution.rs`: pass `&task.repo_url` into git helpers / `ensure_work_branch`.

